  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (NC-9 clean, low-confidence honestly documented)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. All 13 credibility factors are fully assessed with achieved levels meeting or exceeding required levels. One factor (Model form) carries an explicitly-flagged low-confidence score due to wide uncertainty bounds in the hemolysis power-law exponent; this limitation is documented transparently in the rationale and is offset by a conservative Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification envelope that brackets the clinical threshold with 95% confidence. Decision: Accepted with documented residual uncertainty.",
